  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Patients who agree to participate in the study will be asked to sign the informed consent
        and the HIPAA form.

        Inclusive criteria are:

          -  18-75 years of age

          -  ASA physical status I-III

          -  BMI &lt; 35 kg/m2

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  all open shoulder procedures

          -  patient having difficulty understanding the instruction on using the anesthetic
             infusion pump

          -  contraindications to administration of regional anesthesia (e.g., allergy to a local
             anesthetic, local infection and coagulopathy)

          -  significant neurologic disorders of the upper extremity

          -  psychiatric or cognitive disorders

          -  history of substance abuse or chronic opioid use
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
